{"cursor":"6275","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"An 'attribute grammar' is a formal way to define attributes for the productions\nof a formal grammar, associating these attributes to values. The evaluation\noccurs in the nodes of the abstract syntax tree, when the language is processed\nby some parser or compiler.\n\nThe attributes are divided into two groups: synthesized attributes and inherited\nattributes. The synthesized attributes are the result of the attribute\nevaluation rules, and may also use the values of the inherited attributes. The\ninherited attributes are passed down from parent nodes.\n\nIn some approaches, synthesized attributes are used to pass semantic information\nup the parse tree, while inherited attributes help pass semantic information\ndown and across it. For instance, when constructing a language translation tool,\nsuch as a compiler, it may be used to assign semantic values to syntax\nconstructions. Also, it is possible to validate semantic checks associated with\na grammar, representing the rules of a language not explicitly imparted by the\nsyntax definition.\n\nAttribute grammars can also be used to translate the syntax tree directly into\ncode for some specific machine, or into some intermediate language.\n\nOne strength of attribute grammars is that they can transport information from\nanywhere in the abstract syntax tree to anywhere else, in a controlled and\nformal way.\n","linknr":130,"url":"Attribute_grammar","recorded":1364123079,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Attribute_grammar&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Attribute_grammar&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.wikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-head","#p-search","/wiki/Attribute_(computing)","/wiki/Formal_grammar","/wiki/Abstract_syntax_tree","/wiki/Parser","/wiki/Compiler","/wiki/Intermediate_language","/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed","#Example","#Synthesized_attributes","#Inherited_attributes","#Special_types_of_attribute_grammars","#See_also","#External_links","/w/index.php?title=Attribute_grammar&action=edit&section=1","/wiki/Context-free_grammar","/wiki/S-attributed_grammar","/w/index.php?title=Attribute_grammar&action=edit&section=2","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/1/7/b/17b0f5c0cb7b17a6af76a95771303e0c.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/2/8/3/2837ae9ba907dc22c9204c16cf091955.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/f/2/d/f2d8ad6c8eee7080f25f3441c9eaeba2.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/4/4/c/44c29edb103a2872f519ad0c9a0fdaaa.png","/wiki/Formal_grammar#The_syntax_of_grammars","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/5/d/b/5dbc98dcc983a70728bd082d1a47546e.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/2/7/f/27fcb9d89098ecff906ff3aa5f3348da.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/2/d/1/2d1ac1897cdf25b16c34012173267308.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/3/2/7/32758219143c1f0751c18ce70c7f17bb.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/0/5/1/0513fe4b55494f9da3236a12e1a86102.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/a/7/9/a79de83bd36fb2bba7cc9877e8493f63.png","/w/index.php?title=Attribute_grammar&action=edit&section=3","/w/index.php?title=Attribute_grammar&action=edit&section=4","/wiki/S-attributed_grammar","/wiki/L-attributed_grammar","/wiki/Top-down_parsing","/wiki/LR-attributed_grammar","/wiki/Bottom-up_parsing","/wiki/ECLR-attributed_grammar","/w/